 good example of a formidable matriarch, who took a strong lead in managing the family and its resources. Overall, the book provides a full and detailed picture of the family life of an aristocratic family in early modern England. ROSEMARY O'DAY is Professor of History at the Open University and author of, amongst numerous other works, Women's Agency in Early Modern Britain and the American Colonies: Patriarchy, Partnership and Patronage (Pearson. Longman 2007) and Cassandra Brydges (1670-1735) First Duchess of Chandos: Life and Letters (Boydell Press 2007).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aElite (Social sciences)zGreat BritainxHistory. 4aEarly Modern History. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh  aEarly modern England.  aTemples of Stowe.  aaristocratic family.  aestate management.  afamily life.  afamily relationships.  alegal disputes.  asocial networking.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311143106240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781787442719423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781787442719/original  a978-3-11-143106-2  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles